added.title: Second Christmas
added.description: The Titans trick Starfire into believing in second Christmas with second Santa.

added.title: Beast Boy on a Shelf
added.description: Santa Claus forces Beast Boy to become a spy and report on the Titans' naughty behavior.

added.title: Christmas Crusaders
added.description: Santa Claus and Robin must stop the nefarious Coal Miner.

added.title: #SheMightBeGiant
added.description: Karen Beecher is always getting picked on at school, but when the local mall is attacked by a monstrous supervillain called Giganta, she discovers that tiny Bumblebee might be the only one small enough to save the day.

added.title: #FightAtTheMuseum
added.description: Supergirl always relies on her strength, but she'll need more than brawn to stop brainy Catwoman from stealing valuable gems from the local science museum.

added.title: #FromBatToWorse
added.description: Having just moved to the boring Metropolis suburbs, Batgirl is thrilled when she intercepts a call from Batman asking for help. But before she can stop a visiting Gotham villain, she'll have to sneak past her dad, Police Commissioner Gordon.

added.title: #CrushingIt
added.description: Diana Prince is absolutely crushing it in every single aspect of life as a student at Metropolis High, until someone shows up who threatens to throw her off her game for good.

added.title: Lost in the Lost and Found
added.description: When Boss sends Tiggy and Gweeseek into the cellar to fetch a tuba, Tiggy must be brave and overcome his fears of the "Cellar Feller."

added.title: Baby and the Dog
added.description: On a mission to find an orange tennis ball, Tig and Seek encounter their worst nightmares: a baby and a dog. Do they have what it takes to go up against this gruesome twosome and walk away with their ball?

added.title: Sir Tree's Boy
added.description: Seth agrees to take care of Sir Tree's wooden boy, Boy Joy, but quickly pawns him off on Mertha. When Seth discovers that Sir Tree needs his boy back in order to survive, he must stage a heist to steal Boy Joy back before it's too late!

added.title: Mr. Pascal's Opus
added.description: Seth writes a play about the importance of dental hygiene and gets Pascal to direct. Soon the brothers' differences lead to Pascal quitting. But when the star of the show gets stage fright right before curtain, Seth has to get Pascal back!

added.title: Driller
added.description: Panthro is getting a little fed up with having to fix things around the Cats' Lair constantly, which is unfortunate because the ThunderCats are about to be attacked by an unstoppable drilling robot, and he's gonna break everything!

added.title: Secret of the Unicorn
added.description: A crying unicorn appears at the Cats' Lair and weepily tells the ThunderCats that all of her unicorn friends have been captured! Tygra thinks he's just the unicorn expert to help the last of the unicorns, he just needs her to stop sobbing long enough to tell him who took her friends. Easier said than done.

added.title: Panthro Plagiarized!
added.description: Vultureman has got a brand new invention but there's one big problem: he stole the idea from Panthro! Oh, also Vultureman is using his invention to take over Third Earth. So, there are two big problems.

added.title: Warrior Maiden Invasion
added.description: Third Earth is being overrun by super tough, super buff Warrior Maidens and it looks like the ThunderCats are next on their hit list! It's gonna be up to the ThunderKittens to save the day even though the kittens are so small and the Warrior Maidens are so big.

added.title: Lost Sword
added.description: Lion-O is reminded that he needs to plug the Sword of Omens into the Cats' Lair each night or else the base will run out of power. That's fine, it's not like Lion-O's going to accidentally lose the sword or anything. Right?

added.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
added.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

added.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
added.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

added.title: Ninjago Confidential
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, Zane and Pixal hit the mean streets to track down Milton Dyer, only to discover that things are not what they seem.

added.title: The Prodigal Father
added.description: Zane, kidnapped by the Mechanic, faces Unagami. Master Wu fights to free Zane, while Pixal questions Milton Dyer for information on how to shut down Prime Empire.

added.title: The Temple of Madness
added.description: Jay must stand alone against Unagami in the end-game, yet Unagami has a bigger battle in facing the truth about his own identity.

added.title: The Awesome Brawlers vs. Haavik/Their Fights
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers vs. Haavik: Dan and the Awesome brawlers have made their way up Haavik's tower as the final showdown between Haavik and the Awesome Brawlers begins./Their Fights: Haavik's Bakugan battle league rages on in an ultimate showdown between the Awesome Brawlers, vs Haavik and his destructive friends.

added.title: Haavik's Final Show/Miracle Planet
added.description: Haavik's Final Show: It's the final stage of Haavik's Bakugan Battle League: Dan and Drago Infinity vs. Haavik and his six-faction fusion Bakugan, Sabrus. Once again, the fate of two worlds, Earth and Vestoria rests in the hands of the Awesome Brawlers!/ Miracle Planet: The epic clash between Drago Infinty and Sabrus rages on. The winner of this clash of titans will decide the fate Earth and Vestroia.

added.title: Origin of Species
added.description: Origin of Species, Part 1: Dan meets his partner Bakugan Drago for the first time and we learn about the incident that happened on Earth twelve years ago./Origin of Species, Part 2: Dan and friends win the Bakugan Battle, firmly establishing the Awesome Ones as our heroes and Bakugan Brawlers.

added.title: Burger Run/Monkey See, Monkey Don't
added.description: Burger Run: When the local Burger Joint is being threatened by a rogue Bakugan, Dan steps up to save the day and the burgers!/Monkey See, Monkey Don't: The AO stop neighborhood kids from copycat behavior (namely, using their Bakugan for frivolous reasons).

added.title: Bully for You/Trolling for Laughs
added.description: Bully for You: The AO must handle a neighborhood bully who is using his Bakugan to pick on the local kids./Trolling for Laughs: Wynton's constant practical jokes wear thin on his Bakugan Trox so the Bakugan decide to teach him a lesson.

added.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
added.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

added.title: Ninjago Confidencial
added.description: De vuelta en la ciudad de Ninjago, Zane y Pixal salen a las calles para encontrar a Milton Dyer, y descubren que las cosas no son lo que parecen…

added.title: El Padre Prodigo
added.description: Zane, secuestrado por el Mecánico mientras Pixal interroga a Milton Dyer para obtener información sobre cómo cerrar el Primer Imperio.

added.title: El Templo de la Locura
added.description: Jay debe enfrentarse solo a Unagami en el juego final, pero Unagami tiene una batalla más grande al enfrentarse a la verdad sobre su propia identidad.

added.title: Detenerse, Caer y Girar
added.description: Los Ninjas no han ni llorado la pérdida de sus amigos  caídos cuando ya deben entrar a la locura de Tierra Domina.

added.title: El Origen de las Especies Parte 1
added.description: Dan conoce a su pareja Bakugan, Drago, por primera vez y nos enteramos del "incidente" que ocurrió en la Tierra hace doce años.

added.title: El Origen de las Especies Parte 2
added.description: Dan y sus amigos ganan la Batalla Bakugan, demostrando que los Fantásticos son nuestros héroes y los mejores Peleadores Bakugan.

added.title: Un Almuerzo Inesperado
added.description: Cuando el Restaurante de Hamburguesas es amenazado por un violento Bakugan, Dan llega para salvar el día...y las hamburguesas.

added.title: Una Leccion para Todos
added.description: Los Fantásticos le enseñan a unos chicos del vecindario a no imitar a los demás. Por ejemplo, a quienes utilizan a sus Bakugan con fines frívolos.

added.title: El Bravucon
added.description: Los Fantásticos deben lidiar con un bravucón que usa a su Bakugan para intimidar a los chicos del vecindario.

added.title: Bromas Pesadas
added.description: Las constantes bromas pesadas de Wynton colman la paciencia de su Bakugan, Trox, quien decide darle una lección.

added.title: #AunqueSeaGigante
added.description: Karen Beecher siempre es molestada en la escuela. Pero cuando el centro comercial es atacado por una monstruosa super villana llamada Giganta, Karen descubre que la diminuta Bumblebee puede ser la única suficientemente pequeña para salvar el día.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #BatallaEnElMuseo
added.description: Supergirl siempre confía en su fuerza, pero necesitará mas que músculos para impedir que la astuta Catwoman robe unas valiosas gemas del museo de ciencias.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #DeMalEnPeor
added.description: Habiéndose mudado a los aburridos suburbios de Metrópolis, Batgirl se emociona cuando intercepta una llamada de auxilio de Batman. Pero antes de que pueda ir a detener a un villano visitante de Ciudad Gótica, Barbara debe escabullirse de su casa y de su padre, el comisionado Gordon.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #ElFlechazo
added.description: Diana Prince está triunfando en todos los aspectos de la vida y como alumna de la Secundaria Metrópolis... hasta que alguien llega para confundirla totalmente.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Taladro
added.description: Pantro se está hartando de tener que arreglar cosas constantemente por todo el Cubil Felino, lo cual es una pena porque los Thundercats están a punto de ser atacados por un robot perforador imparable...ique va a romper todo!

added.title: Pantro robado
added.description: Buitro tiene un nuevo invento, pero hay un gran problema: ile robó la idea a Pantro! Ah, y además Buitro usa su invento para apoderarse del Tercer Planeta. De modo que hay dos grandes problemas.

added.title: La invasion de las guerreras amazonas
added.description: El Tercer Planeta está siendo invadido por Guerreras Amazonas con fuerza y músculos extraordinarios iy parece que los Thundercats son los siguientes en su lista de ataques! Ahora, la seguridad de todos dependerá de los Thundercachorros, aunque sean tan pequeños y las Guerreras Amazonas sean tan grandes.

added.title: El secreto del unicornio
added.description: Un unicornio que llora aparece en el Cubil Felino y, entre lágrimas, les dice a los Thundercats que todos sus amigos unicornios han sido capturados. Tigro se cree un experto en el tema que podrá ayudar al último de los unicornios...Solo necesita que deje de llorar lo suficiente para decirle quién se llevó a sus amigos. Es más fácil decirlo que hacerlo, viejo.

added.title: La Espada Perdida
added.description: A León-O le recuerdan que debe conectar la Espada del Augurio al Cubil Felino todas las noches o la base se quedará sin energía. No hay problema, no es que León-O vaya a perder accidentalmente la espada o algo así, ¿verdad?
